1 unit Granny Smith Apple
2 slice Sliced Cheddar Cheese
1 unit Demi-Baguette
1.15 ounce Peanut Butter
2 tablespoon Crème Fraîche
½ ounce Pistachios
½ ounce Walnuts
1 ounce Golden Raisins
1 unit Fig Jam
2 teaspoon Honey
Salt
2.5 ounce Celery

• Wash and dry produce.

• Halve, core, and thinly slice apple. Stack cheddar slices and cut into
quarters. Slice baguette into rounds.

• In a small serving bowl, combine peanut butter, crème fraîche, and
a pinch of salt. Stir until smooth. Add 1 TBSP whipped peanut butter
to each celery stick; spread to evenly distribute. Gently press as many
raisins as you like into peanut butter in a single line to create ants on a
log (we used 3-4 raisins for each).

• In a second small serving bowl, combine pistachios and walnuts. TIP: If
you have any leftover raisins, add them to the nut mix!

• Place jam and honey in two separate small serving bowls.

• Arrange apple, cheddar, baguette slices, ants on a log, any remaining
whipped peanut butter, nut mix, jam, and honey on a large serving
board or platter. Serve family style.